Product name: Vintage Isabella Fiore Quality Woven Leather and Fiber Bag with Leather Accent ~ Leather Pine Cones
Description:
This Isabella Fiore bag is so unique that it is hard to describe...it is in the general shape of a wide hobo, with beautifully woven deep reddish brown and chocolate brown nylon fibers and supple chocolate brown leather making up the body.  The gusseted sides and bottom of the bag is made of wonderfully supple chocolate brown leather and supported with a leather and brass strap at each corner.  There are plenty of stylish adornments as well.  The sturdy woven leather strap is backed with soft leather for comfort and attached to the bag with two large bronzed grommets and ring attachments.  But the thing that is most noticeable on this bag is the two large 2 3/4" long pinecones made of leather that hang from the zipper pull!  
The interior is entirely made of  heavy quality brown canvas with leather trim.  There is a metal plate affixed to a large zipper pocket on one side that proclaims "Isabella Fiore" as the maker, and 3 upright slip pockets on the other wall.  The interior measures 9 inches in depth, 17 inches across and 3 3/4 inches wide.
Overall measurements:  Across top from strap to strap: 17 inches; Depth from strap to bottom: 11 inches; Width at widest point: 3 3/4 inches; Strap: 18 inches, which affords a 6 inch drop.
This would make a great "anywhere bag" for your personal use, or an enviable addition to your vintage collection.

Product name: ANTIQUE LACE COLLAR - Large French black lace and bullion collar from the late 1800's
Description:
This spectacular black lace collar dates back to 1880-1890 and comes from France. 
This is a particularly large collar designed, using two sizes of background lace. Nine oval medallions with stemming leaves are spread along the length of the collar, surrounded with a raised scalloped border. The areas  linking the medallions have their own design, resembling large upside down flowers in the back. The edges of the collar towards the front consist of scalloped lace trim, and the pointed ends are adorned with three decorative scrolls. All the designs are made out of rises bullion work.
The lace in the medallions is extremely fine, and as expected for an item that was worn from that time period, there are missing small sections , or little holes, in some areas of the finer lace. The larger woven lace is missing from some of the bigger fields on the back on one side . I suspect the damage was due to too much friction and rubbing in these areas which correspond to were the shoulders are. I am gladly enclosing a 10'' long piece of lace (seen in the last photograph) if you need to make repairs, but when placed on a dark or black fabric, the missing lace seemingly disappears.
The inside length of the collar is 38". The height of the lace in the center of the back is 5 1/8" high and the front lace panels are 4" wide each.

Description:
I offer a flat rate of ¬£3.95 p&p (2nd Class recorded) with no extra charge for additional items, shipping upgrades available at checkout.
Who doesn't love a little delicate, fragrant waft of natural perfume every now and again?
The scents are inspired by the beautiful essential oil blends in our Limited Edition Soap range, as well as some all time favourites of ours from our bathing range.
The wonderful blend of oils, butters and our own Northumbrian Beeswax in these dinky little wonder pots are just waiting to be stroked on to wrists, collar bones, backs of knees...whereever you want to give a delicate fragrance and a little added softness.
Apply as often as needed with the fingertips.

Restful Slumber - Our all time favourite sleepy blend of Sweet Lavender, sharp yet vibrant Bergamot & hauntingly beautiful Neroli oils, stroke on to temples and wrists to help induce a sense of deep calm and relaxation in preparation for a good night's sleep.
Rose Madder - Think of exotic jewel coloured medina's, their lush, cool courtyards, incense smoke curling up to the darkening sky. The corners are piled high with plucked magenta rose blooms drying in the last rays of summer. 'Queen of the Night' flowering jasmine and bright cerise Bougainvillea climb the crumbling stone walls perfuming the air with an intoxicating, heady floral aroma...
Lemon Cream - A pile of fresh Sicilian lemons, sherberty and zesty may chang and rich and sweet creamy vanilla notes from resinous benzoin. Imagine homemade lemonade, and a creamy bowl of meltingly luxurious dairy ice cream, sprinkled with candied lemon peel and sherbet, eaten in the late afternoon sun, under a canopy of vine leaves fringed with gold.
Sweet Orange Floral - Blends of sweet juicy citrus fruits and night flowering jasmine. An ethereal and beautiful yet delicate scent. 
Lavender, Ylang ylang and Patchouli - Sweetly floral and heady Ylang ylang blended beautifully with sharp herbal lavender and the warm earthy notes of dark Indian patchouli oils give this one a distinctive scent that you'll keep reaching for, perhaps my favourite.

Product name: Clam shell seashell mold for cake decorating or polymer clay, beach cakes, gumpaste shell mold, fondant shell mold. M33
Description:
This is a clam shell seashell mold, it's a little over 2" tall and about 2" wide. It can be used for beach cakes, wedding favors, polymer clay and isomalt.
The silicone that I use for these molds is food safe and can be used for gumpaste, fondant, chocolate and sugar. If you use it for non-food purposes don't use it for food too!
I like this individual mold because it's easier to get the shells out without losing the detail on them. Some other multiple-cavity molds that I've used result in flat spots when you push the gumpaste out of the mold, but with this type of silicone it's easier to get the shell out without ruining the detail on it. 
I like this clam shell because it's got such a nice texture on the shell itself. You'll see the detail when you brush it with petal dusts or paint it with food coloring to give it a realistic look. These molds work best with gumpaste or a stiff fondant. Soft fondant won't work in the molds because it will stretch when it's removed and lose the shape and details.

Product name: Universal Stabilizing MEGA FOLDING CONE made of Stainless Steel for all 1/4" inch ‚Äì 3/4" inch Holes in Coin Rings
Description:
This MEGA folding cone can now begin and fully fold over any size coin, round, token or medallion with as small as a 1/4" inch center-punched hole up to as large as a 3/4‚Äù center-punched hole. (Common hole sizes that can be accommodated are: 1/4", 3/8", 7/16", 1/2", 9/16", 5/8", and 3/4").
This tool is another option for those that use an arbor press or a hydraulic press when folding their coin rings.
(NOTE): This tool will NOT work with any ring sizing machines, as there is not enough clearance that's needed. 
* Made from wear resistant and hardened stainless steel, there‚Äôs no more chewed up and worn out plastic folding cones or plastic bearing balls to worry about! 
Here are some reviews that I've received about this tool:
    
"A galaxy of stars wouldn't be enough to select from to reflect in how pleased I am with these new tools. Precision dies and cones and mandrel's epic quality and speedy shipping. I will continue to buy for sure."

      17rem on Feb 16, 2017

--- "Excellent advance and enhancement on original cone - another quality key piece of equipment."
      Garry McNamara on Jan 16, 2017
      5 out of 5 stars 
* MAKE SURE TO WRAP THE MEGA FOLDING CONE WITH PIPE THREAD TAPE PRIOR TO USE TO PROTECT YOUR COIN RINGS‚Äô INNER DETAIL WHILE FOLDING! 
* To use, simply set the coin level into the appropriate-size reduction die, then insert the mega folding cone into the center punched hole to begin folding the coin down into the die. 
MAKE SURE TO USE SEVERAL SHORT STROKES WHILE FOLDING; STOPPING OFTEN TO MAKE SURE THAT YOUR COIN IS LEVEL IN THE REDUCTION DIE. 
The more you fold the coin, the smaller it will become; so you will need to switch to a smaller inner diameter-sized universal reduction die. You continue this process until the sides of the mega folding cone are almost touching the inner portion of your coin. Once that occurs, you have completed the folding process. 
* * * TIPS * * * 
1.)  I like to have the universal reduction die that I am using stacked on top of either the reducing wheel plate from my ring sizer machine or the arbor wheel plate for better stability, (see listing photos for reference.) That way, there‚Äôs enough clearance for the long folding cone to go through without interference. 
2.) You should still bevel (round out) the sharp edges of the hole in your coin BEFORE using this long folding cone, to make sure that there are no micro tears present that can cause your coin to split. (This is best accomplished with a ‚Äúdeburring tool‚Äù that can be purchased online.) 
3.) I like to wrap the mega folding cone with pipe thread tape a few times around, making sure to wrap evenly and to overlap at least half the width of the previous tapes' wrap. Some coins will need more tape, some will need less. I recommend folding over a few clad (non-silver) coins at first for practice.
4.) Make sure to anneal (heat & quench) the coin often to keep the metal in a softer state; as this will make the folding process go smoother with less effort.
This mega folding cone also works great with my set of 2 ‚ÄúStabilizer‚Äù Reduction Dies, as you end up having twice the stability of both the design of the die itself and the long folding cone when folding over any US Quarter, US Half Dollar, Morgan/Peace Dollar, or the American Silver Eagle.
(Coins and coin rings pictured are not included and are meant for reference only).
*** Here‚Äôs why you should purchase this folding tool from the CoinRingUSA Shop:
1. Wear-resistant and hardened stainless steel is used. Each mega folding cone is CNC machined and hand-worked by expert machinists.
2. My customers always come first! I can always be reached through Etsy, by e-mail directly, or by leaving me a comment on my blog site. 
3. The level of quality of my tools is not duplicated elsewhere. 
4. The optimal degree of angle is used on this long folding cone to achieve the best results when folding your coins.
5. I have a passion for both making coin rings as well as creating the highest quality coin ring-making tools on the market today. That's why I've created a platform where people can go to get their questions answered about all things coin rings; as well as ask questions and even leave suggestions. Please visit my new blog site at: www.CoinRingBlog.com for coin ring making tips, tricks, and tool updates. 
6. All of my tools are 100% guaranteed 
7. Why pay a little less for inferior tools? Buy from CoinRingUSA and get the best!
*** SAFETY FIRST ***
--- Always wear safety glasses.
--- Keep fingers, long hair, and loose clothing away from any pinch points or open flame.
--- Make sure to anneal, (heat, then quench) the coin often as you're working it.
